forEach:  Use when you want to perform an action on each item in an array without returning a new array.

map:      Use when you want to transform each item in an array and return a new array of the same length.

filter:   Use when you want to select items based on a condition and return a new array with only those items.

reduce:   Use when you want to combine all items in an array into a single value (e.g., sum, object, string).